+{"id":"frankenjax-p2vi","title":"Avoid holding LRU order lock during backend eviction","description":"Skill: /deadlock-finder-and-fixer\n\nVerified hazard: crates/fj-cache/src/eviction.rs LruCache::enforce_budget holds the internal order Mutex while invoking CacheBackend::stats and CacheBackend::evict. CacheBackend is a public trait for arbitrary backends, so calling backend code while holding the wrapper lock creates a reentrancy/deadlock hazard if a backend observes or re-enters the LRU wrapper, logs through shared cache state, or blocks behind code that needs the order lock.\n\nReproduction target: add a custom test backend whose stats/evict methods try_lock the LruCache order mutex. On the current implementation, inserting beyond max_entries or max_bytes fails because enforce_budget still holds order while calling into the backend.\n\nExpected fix: shorten the order critical section, pop eviction keys into local values, drop the lock, and only then call backend stats/evict. Keep LRU ordering behavior unchanged and add a regression test that proves backend calls are made without the order lock held.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T20:03:12.272682861Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T20:07:49.435391870Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T20:07:49.433312595Z","close_reason":"Completed: moved LRU budget eviction backend calls outside the order mutex critical section and added a reentrancy regression test proving backend stats/evict run without the order lock held.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
